public interface MkvSupply

      • getCharSequence

        CharSequence getCharSequence​(int idx)
                      throws MkvException
        Returns a CharSequence associated the field at the specified position.

        CharSequence are mutable, objects returned by this method should not be cached, but they may be used for copying the values into string buffers, thus avoiding unnecessary String object allocations.

        Parameters:

      • getObject

        Object getObject​(int idx)
          throws MkvException
        Returns the Object value of the field at the specified position.

        Integer, Date an Time values are returned as Integer objects, Double values as Double objects, String values as CharSequence objects.
